&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title&lt;/strong&gt;: CFO-in-Residence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;: Remote (with occasional travel as needed)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;: At &lt;strong&gt;Shaper Capital&lt;/strong&gt;, we’re on a mission to partner with incredible people to build companies that shape the world. Shaper Capital was founded by Travis May, who led the two biggest data companies created in the last 20 years (LiveRamp and Datavant); we’ve launched six companies over the past year, creating data businesses that follow similar playbooks across industries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By joining Shaper today, you’ll be part of a small, ambitious team driven by the belief that the world’s greatest problems have yet to be solved and the most transformative companies have yet to be built. We empower our portfolio companies to create businesses that transform industries, and we believe in hiring individuals who are &lt;strong&gt;smart, nice, and get things done&lt;/strong&gt;. We invest in hiring high potential and humble individuals who thrive in fast-paced, ambiguous environments and can rapidly grow their responsibilities as we reimagine company creation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re building a “&lt;strong&gt;CFO-in-Residence&lt;/strong&gt;” program to identify and cultivate the next wave of finance leaders for Shaper’s portfolio. This is a unique opportunity for strategic finance professionals to work across multiple early-stage, venture-backed startups—initially supporting them on a &lt;strong&gt;fractional basis&lt;/strong&gt;, and over time, growing into &lt;strong&gt;full-time Head of Finance or CFO roles&lt;/strong&gt; as mutual fit emerges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As CFO-in-Residence, you’ll partner closely with founders to build the financial foundation of their companies. You might help close a fundraise, set up financial systems, build operating models, or shape pricing and monetization strategies. Each tour of duty is high-leverage, fast-paced, and critical to company success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires someone who thrives in early-stage environments, is eager to solve complex financial challenges, and is comfortable operating both at a strategic level and in the financial trenches.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Embed with Portfolio Companies: &lt;/strong&gt;Serve as a fractional Head of Finance or strategic finance partner to 1–2 Shaper-backed companies at a time, supporting mission-critical needs during moments of growth, fundraising, or operational scale-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own Core Finance Functions: &lt;/strong&gt;Stand up or refine financial systems, develop budgets, forecasts, and dashboards, and help establish key KPIs to support board-level reporting and decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support Fundraising: &lt;/strong&gt;Partner with founders on modeling, storytelling, data room readiness, and investor Q&amp;amp;A&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build Scalable Infrastructure: &lt;/strong&gt;Lay the groundwork for long-term success by establishing best practices in financial operations, cash management, vendor selection, and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Projects: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead one-off strategic finance initiatives, including pricing strategy, cap table modeling, M&amp;amp;A diligence, cost optimization, or international expansion planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grow Into Permanent Roles: &lt;/strong&gt;Over time, transition into a full-time CFO or Head of Finance position within a portfolio company that’s the right mutual fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;We are looking for Shapers to help create and lead exceptional companies. We aspire to build the highest-performing team in the world by bringing together ambitious people who are smart, nice, and get things done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot;&gt;Shaper Capital and its portfolio companies are hiring for many roles, including but not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-rte-list=&quot;default&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shaper Fellows &amp;amp; CEOs&lt;/strong&gt; — relentlessly entrepreneurial, ridiculously ambitious, brilliant, and ethical leaders who can help launch businesses, turn ideas into execution, and lead companies as they scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operations Partners&lt;/strong&gt; — help us build the infrastructure for building and shaping companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Software Engineers &amp;amp; Product Managers &lt;/strong&gt;— for our portfolio of companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;— What are you exceptional at? Write your own job description.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot;&gt;All Shapers receive equity in the businesses they build. Our objective is to create the most competitive risk-reward package, the biggest opportunity to shape industries, and the best environment in the world for personal growth. We do this by pairing Shapers with business ideas that we are uniquely positioned to pursue, supplying the capital and assets needed for rapid growth, and providing hands-on support in building a bu&lt;span class=&quot;sqsrte-text-color--white&quot;&gt;siness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

